Jump-Start Lets assume we have the following Java class, and we want to compile it to JavaScript and run it in the Browser:
package bytecodertest; public class HelloWorld { public static void main(String[] args) { System.out.println(&quot;Hello World!&quot;); } }  First of all, we need to compile the Java sources to a JVM class file. This is done by using the javac tool from the JDK:
javac HelloWorld.java  Now, we have the compiled .
